divs: Sighting DetailsI was using a lens on my Canon 5d that is not made for a full frame sensor thus the vignetting around the edge of the frame. I was taking pictures of a rainbow and in a series of shot from the same angle this shot was a middle one and shows a bizarre object. I thought maybe a it was sensor dust that is not the case because none of the other in the series shows this defect. This looks like a stealth aircraft closeup but I am not sure what it is. Look to the top left corner of the image.
